I used to fear self-improvement, because I feared what others would think.  People don't just "up and change". The status quo mindset weighed heavy.  I had a hard time accepting change in others, as well as change for myself.

To break free of this mindset often feels like pulling teeth. 
But here's the truth of the matter: 
People CAN change.
People DO change.

And we can either choose to accept it for ourselves and others, or sit in an attitude of disbelief and disgust.  The latter, I've found, is often out of a heart of unrealized pain and unforgiveness.  It's a spirit of placing others in the box we ourselves are trapped, where pride, misunderstanding, and nonacceptance reign. 
No one is perfect, and we are all on different paths in our journeys.  Some have conquered the steep, rocky terrains.  Others are still learning how to maneuver.  Don't ever feel you are too above the ones struggling, just because you've made it to the top.  And to those, like me, who are still learning, don't let the discouragement of where you are now dismay you.  Encourage those behind you, and move towards your goal.  Rise above the status quo, be gracious and compassionate to those still struggling, and fear not the wonderful changes that will occur.
This is all about a long process ... enjoying all the processes ... and being healthier every day... #health #healthier #process #everydaygetsbetter

Failure is a necessary part of growth, and in the process of realizing your dreams. Failure is never fatal and it's not a dead end. Failure leads you to an unexpected reward, if you're receptive. Failure is nothing more than consistent incorrect actions, as a result of an error in judgement, over an extended period of time. When we stop for a minute to evaluate why what we're doing isn't working, we open up the door to receive the formula to make that step in the process work. Failure will only defeat a quitter, but failure is the launching pad for a winner. A winner will take what there is to learn from the failure and use it to correct the course, thus implementing the proper actions as a result of correct judgement. Actions implemented from correct judgement over and extended period of time has no choice but to yield success in the long run. Don't be afraid of failure. Failure is what is needed to learn and grow. Failure strengthens the mind and forces you to think like the person you need to become, in order to achieve your goal. #failure#learn#resilience#growthhack#grow#success#trialanderror#process#instagood#instadaily#instamood#goodmorning#motivationalquotes#quoteoftheday#good#reads#books#goodreads#audiobook#audiobooks#life#good#people

I believe art should be FUN!!!And you should EARN an A if you want one!!! So I give endless extra credit of various tasks aimed to make my students better, while earning extra points along the way!  This student, who I'm sure already had an A, earned even more points for throwing, trimming and then cutting her bowl in half!!!! And before we cut it open she already knew that it would be a little bit thick, after all, she did throw and trim it all in one class period! 🙌🙌🙌 Sooooo proud of all of my students' growth this semester!!! 👏👏👏😊😊😊
